BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:eu-ai-act-2025-02-02@enterpriseai.tools
DTSTAMP:20260718T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20250202
SUMMARY:EU AI Act: Prohibited AI practices and AI literacy
DESCRIPTION:In force. Bans on unacceptable-risk practices (Article 5) and
  deployer AI-literacy duties (Article 4) apply. Source: https://digital-
 strategy.ec.europa.eu/en/policies/regulatory-framework-ai
URL:https://www.enterpriseai.tools/eu-ai-act/
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:eu-ai-act-2025-08-02@enterpriseai.tools
DTSTAMP:20260718T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20250802
SUMMARY:EU AI Act: Governance rules and general-purpose AI model obligati
 ons
DESCRIPTION:In force. GPAI model transparency obligations and the AI Act 
 governance bodies apply\; Commission enforcement powers over GPAI provid
 ers begin 2 August 2026. Source: https://digital-strategy.ec.europa.eu/e
 n/policies/regulatory-framework-ai
URL:https://www.enterpriseai.tools/eu-ai-act/
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:eu-ai-act-2026-08-02@enterpriseai.tools
DTSTAMP:20260718T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260802
SUMMARY:EU AI Act: Most AI Act obligations\, including Annex III high-ris
 k systems
DESCRIPTION:Legally in force on this date under the adopted AI Act. The D
 igital Omnibus on AI (provisional agreement May 2026\, close to adoption
  — not yet published in the Official Journal) would defer stand-alone An
 nex III high-risk obligations to 2 December 2027. Source: https://www.eu
 roparl.europa.eu/legislative-train/package-digital-package/file-digital-
 omnibus-on-ai
URL:https://www.enterpriseai.tools/eu-ai-act/
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:eu-ai-act-2027-08-02@enterpriseai.tools
DTSTAMP:20260718T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20270802
SUMMARY:EU AI Act: High-risk AI systems embedded in regulated products
DESCRIPTION:Application date for Annex I product-embedded high-risk syste
 ms under the adopted AI Act. The Digital Omnibus on AI would defer this 
 to 2 August 2028 (provisional\, pending formal adoption). Source: https:
 //www.europarl.europa.eu/legislative-train/package-digital-package/file-
 digital-omnibus-on-ai
URL:https://www.enterpriseai.tools/eu-ai-act/
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
